st - simple terminal
====================
st is a simple terminal emulator for X which sucks less.

Heavily modified st build for my daily use. All patches inspected
refactored and fully integrated. Liberal changes to the source code
driven by personal preference. Keyboard shortcuts documented in the
manual and other relevant functionality listed below.

credit
------
fork of <https://st.suckless.org>.

install
-------
`sudo make install clean`

manual
------
`man st`

patch
-----
- [gruvbox-material](https://st.suckless.org/patches/gruvbox-material)
  color scheme

- [vertcenter](https://st.suckless.org/patches/vertcenter)
  vertical center

- [delkey](https://st.suckless.org/patches/delkey)
  delete key

- [spoiler](https://st.suckless.org/patches/spoiler)
  invisible text selection

- [boxdraw](https://st.suckless.org/patches/boxdraw)
  line rendering consistency

- [title_parsing_fix](https://st.suckless.org/patches/title_parsing_fix)
  window title semicolons

- [csi_22_23](https://st.suckless.org/patches/csi_22_23)
  window title stack
  + code refactor

- [undercurl](https://st.suckless.org/patches/undercurl)
  underline extensions
  + less memory usage
  + csi parsing fix
  + custom render

- [scrollback](https://st.suckless.org/patches/scrollback)
  history buffer
  + scrollback mark
  + custom ringbuffer
  + scroll hide and clear
  + selection compatibility
  + resize compatibility
  + lazy allocation

- [externalpipe](https://st.suckless.org/patches/externalpipe)
  terminal content pipe
  + command line option
  + scrollback compatibility

- [columnredraw](https://st.suckless.org/patches/columnredraw)
  clipped text persistence
  + scrollback compatibility

- cursor restore
  + multiple registers
  + scrollback compatibility
